commitResults.messageBody:
There are currently checks to make sure that the time variable of
the 2 class are not null

But by adding the assert statement to make sure that the variables are
not null will ensure that there
is no chance of a nullPointerException happening when the toString()
method is used

Add assert statement to check that the time variable in the 2 classes
are not null during construction of the Task object.

commitResults.messageTitle: A-CodeQuality Fix Parser.java catch DukeException where it returns an arbitrary string  instead of getting the message from the exception, also check through for any code quality violations and attempt to mitigate/fix.
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously added overloaded constructor for DukeException to create DE
with custom messages but did not change Parser.java catch behavior to
accommodate change

Change catch statement to get message from exception instead of return
arbitrary error message.

commitResults.messageTitle: C-Update Add edit method to TaskList.java as well as support of "edit" keyword in  Parser.java, add setDescription, setDate, setTime for Task
commitResults.messageBody:
Add new feature to Duke, allow user to edit their existing tasks to
 change description, date or time with cmd "edit [task index number]
 /[task type eg.description, date or time] [what to replace with]. Task
 now include Date and Time variable so Event and Deadline can set date
 and time easily while it should not matter to the ToDo class as it is
 never initialized.
